        <strong><h3>REMEMBER TO SIGN OUR PETITION AT http://chng.it/Z8k76g5d7K</h3></strong>
        <h2>Nitrates & Nitrites</h2>
        <p>Nitrate is formed when nitrite (NO2-) comes into contact with water. 
        The nitrogen (N2) reacts with the water and forms nitrate (NO3-) because of the close relationship between the nitrate and the nitrite. 
        When the N2 reacts with the H2O, it causes the oxygen molecules to break apart from the water molecule. 
        The oxygen reacts with the nitrogen and forms nitric oxide (NO), then the nitric oxide is (NO) oxidized to form nitrogen dioxide (NO2). 
        From there, the nitrogen dioxide reacts to the water and turns the nitrogen dioxide to nitric acid (HNO3), which can result in chemical burns.</p>
        <p></p>
